                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d463">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.811/8–2048: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Austria</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Erhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vienna</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-08-20">August 20,
                            1948</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1017. Council of Ministers issued statement yesterday that Austria is not bound
                    by Danube agreement concluded by eastern countries; and that as soon Austria can
                    take part as member with full rights in negotiations concerned with this
                    question it will undertake examination of merits of this agreement.</p>
                <p>Sent Dept; repeated Belgrade as 337.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Erhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
